      • setMethodContent

        void setMethodContent(java.lang.String filePath)
               throws DfException
        Sets the content of the method. This replaces any existing content of the method and sets the method to use its content. After the method is saved, the content is removed from the local file system.
        Parameters:
        filePath - The path of the method content.
        Throws:
        DfException

      • removeMethodContent

        void removeMethodContent()
                  throws DfException
        Removes the content of the method. No exception is thrown if there is no content in this method intially. If there is a content file in the file system, this removes the file from the file system.
        Throws:
        DfException

      • hasMethodContent

        boolean hasMethodContent()
                  throws DfException
        Indicates if this method has content.
        Returns:
        True means this method has content. False otherwise.
        Throws:
        DfException

      • getMethodContent

        java.lang.String getMethodContent()
                           throws DfException
        Gets the content of the method.
        Returns:
        The path of the method content if any. If there is no content, this is null.
